---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';

const title = 'About';
const description = 'About Ben Balter and this Astro implementation';
---

<PageLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <section>
    <h2>Project Context</h2>
    <p>
      This Astro project is part of Ben Balter's personal website repository, 
      which is currently exploring multiple static site generation approaches:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Jekyll (Legacy)</strong> - The original implementation, currently in production</li>
      <li><strong>Next.js (In Development)</strong> - A React-based migration with App Router</li>
      <li><strong>Astro (Experimental)</strong> - This implementation, exploring Astro's capabilities</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  
  <section>
    <h2>Why Astro?</h2>
    <p>
      Astro offers several advantages for static sites:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Performance First</strong> - Ships zero JavaScript by default</li>
      <li><strong>Component Islands</strong> - Partial hydration for interactive components</li>
      <li><strong>Framework Agnostic</strong> - Use React, Vue, Svelte, or plain HTML</li>
      <li><strong>Built-in Optimizations</strong> - Image optimization, asset bundling, and more</li>
      <li><strong>Great DX</strong> - Fast builds, hot module reloading, TypeScript support</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  
  <section>
    <h2>Configuration</h2>
    <p>This Astro project is configured to coexist with existing implementations:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Build output: <code>dist-astro/</code> (separate from Jekyll <code>_site/</code> and Next.js <code>out/</code>)</li>
      <li>Development server: Port 4321 (Jekyll uses 4000, Next.js uses 3000)</li>
      <li>Source directory: <code>src/</code> (Astro-specific)</li>
      <li>Static assets: <code>public/</code> at repository root (shared with Next.js)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  
  <section>
    <h2>GitHub Pages Compatibility</h2>
    <p>
      The Astro build is configured for static site generation with:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Static output mode (no server-side rendering)</li>
      <li>Trailing slashes for consistent URLs</li>
      <li>Directory-based output format</li>
      <li>Optimized asset handling</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
